[code snippet 1]
```java
// Vulnerable code
import java.io.IOException;
import java.io.PrintWriter;
import java.sql.Connection;
import java.sql.DriverManager;
import java.sql.PreparedStatement;
import java.sql.ResultSet;
import java.sql.SQLException;

public class VulnerableServlet {
    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException {
        // Connect to the database
        Connection conn = DriverManager.getConnection("jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/mydb", "username", "password");
        PreparedStatement stmt = conn.prepareStatement("SELECT * FROM users WHERE username =?");
        stmt.setString(1, request.getParameter("username"));
        ResultSet result = stmt.executeQuery();

        // Print the result
        PrintWriter out = response.getWriter();
        out.println("<html><body>");
        while (result.next()) {
            out.println(result.getString("username") + "<br>");
        }
        out.println("</body></html>");
    }
}
```
***

[code snippet 2]
```java
// Fixed code
import java.io.IOException;
import java.io.PrintWriter;
import java.sql.Connection;
import java.sql.DriverManager;
import java.sql.PreparedStatement;
import java.sql.ResultSet;
import java.sql.SQLException;

public class FixedServlet {
    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException {
        // Connect to the database
        Connection conn = DriverManager.getConnection("jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/mydb", "username", "password");
        PreparedStatement stmt = conn.prepareStatement("SELECT * FROM users WHERE username =?");
        stmt.setString(1, request.getParameter("username").trim()); // Trim the input to prevent SQL injection
        ResultSet result = stmt.executeQuery();

        // Print the result
        PrintWriter out = response.getWriter();
        out.println("<html><body>");
        while (result.next()) {
            out.println(result.getString("username") + "<br>");
        }
        out.println("</body></html>");
    }
}
```
In the vulnerable code snippet, the `request.getParameter("username")` method is used to get the username from the request without any validation or sanitization. This makes the code vulnerable to SQL injection attacks, as an attacker could inject malicious SQL code into the `username` parameter.

In the fixed code snippet, the `request.getParameter("username").trim()` method is used to trim the input to prevent SQL injection attacks. This ensures that any malicious characters in the input are removed, making the code more secure.

